.
🧘‍♀️Gentle yoga is a great action you can take to send signals to your mind & body of safety.
.
❤This helps to reinstate the parasympathetic nervous system, counteract the causes of anxiety, reduce the stress hormones, increase oxygen & release tension. Plus it's a nice thing to do, this gets you off your phone &  reconnecting to things that matter.
.
🧎‍♂️Many people find joy in this practice, so give it a try & let us know how you found it, everyone is different!
.
😊Check out @maracimatoribus she has some great videos for you to try, see what works for you!

#anxiety #feelinganxious #action #yourcontrol #practice #interesing #new #try #anxietymanagement

.
👍Both myself & Priyanka @almaformula have collaborated to bring you this challenge & we will both be taking part.
.
🤔We will be consciously working on what we are in control of : behaviours such as 
.
Daily habits
Food choices
Thought Management
Morning rituals
Reconnecting to nature
etc.

All these will impact our thoughts & feelings.
Reduce fear
Reduce anxiety
Boost wellbeing & immunity.
Win Win Win!
.
👉Each weekend we will go live for a Q & A. After the live, we will be posting up what you need, to be prepared for the week. (things you may already have or are very affordable to get) So that you don't arrive at one day and think "I am not ready" & then decide you can't join in. 
.
👉Each evening between 9pm French time we will be posting up what to do for the following day.
So that you know what to expect, as some of the activities are designed to be, as you wake up.
.
👉You can follow myself & @almaformula we will be doing the challenge ourselves & documenting this in our stories to give you two different perspectives from the challenge as well as your own. 
.
👉There will be links given as we go, for ideas, downloadables etc. as part of the challenge. 
.
👉If you are thinking you can't do this, it may be too long?
.
👉HERE'S a Helpful perception
Life sometimes happens, even myself, I may have a day when it's not possible to achieve that days activity, like too many urgent things may take over. That's fine & not a reason to beat myself up or decide I've failed, feel bad & the choose to not take part the next day. No i'll take the day I need & will be ready the next day.
.
👉Also this is a challenge to be taken with interest & discovery of self. To become aware of what behaviours we choose that may influence our thoughts & feelings. Not to tell ourselves off, but to know where we can make the first step.
.
👉We are in control of our behaviours & this will impact/influence on our though & feelings.
.
👉Up next is the shopping list.
👉Sunday 9pm gmt +1 Monday's challenge Will be posted.
👉Monday websites & links to what you need.
👉Everything will be saved in the highlights & IGTV for you to try at any time.
.
😊

WHY Is it sometimes hard to find something grateful? It's normal if you find it hard, there is alot of uncertainty & new information everyday. causing us to feel anxious bit try not to let that stop you taking control of reconnecting to nice thoughts & nice feelings. now more than ever you need it. ❤
.
Watch this to help you.
.
#30daygratefulchallenge 📲for 30 days take a picture of something you have noticed cheered you up, no people.
Go to your stories
Add the picture 
and write on it using text.

#30daygratefulchallenge
TAG us @anxiety_wellbeing
.
Write what three things you found lifted your spirits that day.
look for the good.
.
Add a song to it, upbeat or calm.
.
Save it in your highlights
.
Start building your feel good library
.
The intention is not to impress but to show how the little things you already have really matter & bring good feelings.
.
You can go the highlights for some grateful inspiration. .
I look forward to seeing your tags 😊 I will spend one hour a day reposting your challenges. ❤
.
#anxiety #anxietycoach #positive #wellness #copingskills #emotionalmanagement #resilience #recovery #rejuvenate #wellness #selfhelp #selfhelper #cbt #support #feelgood #control

node.text:
So why 𝗴𝘂𝗲𝘀𝘀? We think we can read minds, & read facial expressions. Most of the time we can't, that look is nothing to do with you. How can you change that?❤👇
.
🎨@hazel.mead 🌎🌱
✒@anxiety_wellbeing
.
ANXIETY 
Can be caused by thinking that you are able to read a mind, your unconcious or subconcious thoughts will connect that idea with old past hurtful scenarios & voila you've got yourself a miss communication, the wrong idea based on- ideas & emotions but no blooming FACTS, feeling tough emotions.
.
TIMES I've got it very wrong.
.
Example.
What I thought about me & HOW I was perceived.
Girls@ secondary school
.
😶5 years: I thought that, people didn't think of me as much, maybe just one of the crowd that fits in. I was always concious of keeping myself to myself, I made friends with all groups, but never a close 1-2-1. I thought the looks were, them knowing I had been bullied before & was vulnerable.
.
After 5 years at school, we were saying goodbye at 16. We all wrote notes to eachother. They said. We thought you were so strong. So put together, like nothing could touch you. We thought you were very pretty.🙄
.
🌱Huh! What sorry, you thought what?
I wasn't being perceived as I thought I was. I was guessing based on previous pain from junior school. I got it WRONG.
.
Example.
😶A time at work, I was 22. A girl seemed to stop talking to me, I thought, 'ah she doesn't like me, this happened at junior school, shes about to get nasty' she was head down, staying out of conversations. I thought everything she was doing was to myself. I stressed when I saw her. I avoided talking too. Then one night we got talking. Turns out she was having a lot of trouble with a boyfriend, it was getting quite nasty & she didn't feel she could tell anyone.
.
🌱I was WRONG. She had her own issues. & I equated her behaviour to be about me.
.
🌱I'VE learned 
We naturally guess that we know why someone is acting that way or what they are thinking & we DON'T. 
Usually the guess is connected to a past experience, usually unconsciously.
.
🌱Practice awareness
Does it feel like something before?
It's probubly nothing to do with you.
Try not to react.
.
#anxiety #selfhelpers

node.text:
Unfortunately, most of us have 𝗹𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗻𝘁 from school & parents etc, that what you do is the reason you get good or bad feed back & we perceive that to = your worth👇
.
🎨@newhappyco 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
Examples

⚠️Crying is bad
👍Being quite is good
.
(Why's is it perceived as bad? Because imperfect humans don't all know how to self regulate their emotions, so your emotions are extra)
.
⚠️Low school grades is bad
👍High school grades is good
.
(Why is it perceived as bad? Because there is a belief that your grades define you, when actually its a sign of👉Was the information presented the way you connect to info, for your needs? There is still some things that you need some help with. A grade is a sign of what you know/remembered & that you can repeat that info in an exam. That's it)
.
⚠️Working your socks of is good
👍Taking a break is bad
.
(Why is a break perceived bad? Because some have the belief that stopping & taking a break is lazy. Of course this is not true but they are afraid of opinion & that drives their words & actions)
.
⚠️Getting it on your own is amazing 
👍Asking a question is bad "why don't you know?"
.
(Why cant you ask a question? Some people think questions are stupid & that is meant you don't get it but a question is the most intelligent thing you could do. It means you want to understand & gain insight)
.
We are meaning making beings & all through your life examples like these will go towards what you believe about yourself & the world you're in.
.
Am I enough just being me, learning, growing?
.
Well examples like these can give the you perception that your worth is based around this but ITS NOT.
.
Guess what?
Ideas, perceptions, beliefs are leanrt & can evolve & change, ask yourself are they limiting? 
.
Its normal with examples like these that you've picked up a limiting belief or too but the TRUTH IS you were/are always enough, & always will be.❤
.
Tell yourself that daily, this helps reduce the fear that you must perform & reducing fear means you will be much better able to do the things that will help you to add purpose to your life & for others.
.
#anxiety #anxietycoach #anxietyhelp #perception #human #wellbeing #thrive

🔴MUST READ🔴👇This is certainly how we can feel but its not anxiety making you angry its......👇
.
🎨@allyse_has_anxiety 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
Thanks allyse for these slides that are very relatable, I too used to be angry at anxiety.
.
That was until I understood that its not the response making you angry its what you perceived it means to you that then impacts thoughts and feelings.
.
Anxiety response is fight flight or freeze a perceived danger, but how you perceive anxiety to be = your following response to anxiety 
.
Examples
.
😡Anxiety Perceived as the problem
.
💭Oh no im feeling anxious 
This is terrible
What have I done?
There's nothing I can do!
Its out to get me!
Fuking anxiety!😤
.
Others perceived as the problem 
💭Noone gets it
They should!😤
.
💭Someone might upset me today & I'll be anxious 
They should know how I feel.😤
.
Me perceived as the problem
💭Why can't I stop this
I'm silly, stupid!😤
.
💭I can't control my thoughts
I should be able to!😤
.
.
🌱🌱🌱🌱🌱🌱🌱🌱
.
Perceptions can be changed 
.
😇Perceived as a safe = difuse
Felling anxious
.
💭I feel anxious today
What do I need? My mind and body are telling me i need to put a change in my day.
I can Counteract 
Take in some breaths
Try to release tension 
Write down worries
Take a break
Make sure I eat something nutritional 
Say no to somethings 
Etc
.
💭I feel noone gets it
But then I remember that before I felt this anxious I had no idea how this felt either l willl try to talk to a friend anyway. No expectations.
.
💭Try no to expect someone will upset you, remember noone knows how you feel, that cannot guess & if someone does say something, you do not have to react, you can retreat & walk away. I've got to get going thanks.
.
💭I can't stop the response to a cause, all I can do is counteract. Thats what I can do.
.
💭The more I think I should control my thoughts the more I am focused on them.
I accept this thought, I accept it's not me but a thought from an influence I've seen, heard etc before. I gently distract myself. What would I do if I won the lottery? What three wishes would I make of i could. 
.
#anxiety #anxietyhelp

node.text:
You do not have to tell 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝗼𝗻𝗲 how you really feel, because some are available to listen & some are not. Choose the odd person to be honest with & keep it there.
.
🎨@yallah 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
🌱Yes lie, lie so that you do not have to explain why you feel that way, so that noone guesses why, so that there is no judgement or misunderstanding.
.
🌱We get the impression that we should be honest & we should but not with everyone. Its exhausting trying to explain yourself & not everyone is able to react to this without their own emotions involved.
.
🌱Plus to explain everything you need to tell everything that has been happening to gain an understanding of roughly why. That takes a while.
.
🌱Don't get me wrong, noone is being a bad person here, we are all human & not perfect. We can be open to learning or closed off to what we have learnt in ideas or perceptions that we are not willing to relook at. We could also be struggling with our own emotions & issues etc. 
.
🌱Example.
You tell a mate, 🙎‍♀️🗣I've been feeling anxious
& they might think 👩‍🦳💭'i can't deal, I've got my own issues' & then come across short & change the subject. This does not make them, a bad person & does not mean that you should not talk or you've done something wrong. No its makes us all human with our own issues & not all equipped at that time to do whats best for the other. Each one with their own need & unable to meet the others need.
.
🙎‍♀️I need to express how I've been feeling
👩‍🦳I need to set boundaries because I am overwhelmed too. 
.
🌱This means choose who you get honest with, you only need one or two for this & then you can listen to them when they need.
.
🌱It sometimes takes a while to find your honest tribe & to create one you also have to be open & non judgemental for it to be beneficial & feel truly safe to express.
.
Keep looking.
.
#anxiety #anxietycoach #copingskills #perception #anxietyhelp #new #ideas #trust #safe #tribe #honest #choose

It's 𝗻𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿 too late! You know when you're sitting there & thoughts pop up saying, 💭 I've not done that thing I said I wanted to do by now, I am getting older, its too late. Well 👇
.
 📽@cycasmotivation 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
👉A thought if believed or 
A thought that causes sufficient emotion like fear, anxiety, feeling low
Can be the only thing stopping you.
.
👉A thought it not a fact, it might feel like it, but it is not.
.
👉Today, this Sunday, if you are worried, or down, or upset, frustrated you arnt where enough wanted to be in life. Take a deep breath my lovely, it not too late, and have evrthing in you to learn & grow.

👉Let me tell you something, I didn't start realising my strengths until I was 30, I didn't know what I wanted to do until 35. It took 8 years to get here (giving away my age) and if I had believed it was too late, I would not have started & of i had not started, this account would not be here & I wouldn't be helping as many people as I can exit anxiety & thrive 😊 If I decided on my actions based on how I felt, I would be nowhere near this.
.
👉One of the reasons it took till now was I put my energy where it was going nowhere & that left zero energy to put it into myself or even ask what I really wanted.
.
👉It's not too late to learn, connect, grow, decide, change your mind or mindset, etc.
.
👉Let this be the knowledge that brings you peace, do that you can allow yourself to enjoy today ❤
.
Enjoy the present moment, love, connect, do what you love.
.
#anxiety #joy #grow #human #anxietyhelp #anxietycoach

node.text:
Breathe in, then if you start 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 about stuff that worries you, try this......👇
.
🎨@steinbergdrawscartoons 
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
👉It is normal to try to calm the mind & find that it doesn't just switch off when you decide "ok right now I'm going to switch off" doesn't work like this.
.
👉If anything it will feel as though it just speed up, & realising that might scare you.
.
👉Why does it feel like it speed up? 
Because we have so many distractions in our life we don't realise how much info is being processed up there, or that we have a choice or not.🧠
.
👉Think about 1 hour of scrolling (and im being naive here, most of us find ourselves scrolling for hours) how much info, images, ideas, thoughts, worries, fears, dreams etc do you get though in that hour? Thousands......
.
👉So when we ask the mind to just stop, its still trying to process all that info, It takes time to slow down.
.
👉Then also, if you think straight away it won't work, breathing in & out won't work & then decide its because you can't or are not able, the combination feeling shocked by a racing mind & your own beliefs causes fear & fear causes anxiety. Then once anxious (stress response) the mind is automatically focused on negative (danger) & because of what you may believe or tell yourself the danger could be focused on, I make mistakes, its me 😔. 
.
👉So when you take time to breathe,

Make sure you have given yourself ample time
Breathe all the way to your tummy for 4
Hold for 7
Release tension on the exhale for 8.
.
👉You may notice the mind is still running
Remind yourself your mind needs time to slow & it will
Speak to yourself
I may have worries but they are not true
Mistakes are the way that you learn
I am safe
I am enough
I am energising myself
I am taking this time to disconnect from the distractions 
I am reconnecting to my breath
I am reconnecting to calm
I release tension.
I will imagine myself right now at.
The beach🏖
The park🖼
My favorite place🏡
A calm lake 🏡
In the sun🌞
In a shady spot🌳
Etc.
.
Wherever you sense would be a nice place to take that mini break in your mind.
.
#anxiety #anxietycoach #anxietyhelp #beach #lake #tension #tobe #human #

HAVE you ever 𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗱 supporting yourself? Your inner voice can be a big cause for anxiety. How?👇🏼
.
🎨@spiritdaughter 😊
✒@anxiety_wellbeing
.
This is great advice for supporting another human through lifes, trials, tribulations, challenges, uncertanty, its all normal. What we need is to be able to speak & say how we feel.
.
TALK thought it with someone who listens.
This process is magic for validating your feelings & having a way to find solutions.
.
DID YOU KNOW YOU CAN BE THAT PERSON?❤
.
LET'S imagine that when you stop for a second to think, "what was that I was just thinking?" you discover that in a moment of
Stress
Challenge
Uncertainty
You've said to yourself subconsciously or consciously👇🏼
.
🗣I feel like I NEED to cry this is tough, I am being silly. Stop it now.
.
🗣You SHOULD know what your doing, how come you don't know?
.
🗣I feel my body feels a bit ANXIOUS. Just say it's ok just keep going.
.
🗣I FEEL like I was once in this situation before, why does this keep happening? Why me?
.
🗣I am FOCUSED on how I am, I feel down.
.
This way of speaking to yourself is another way to shut down what you need. To block your own growth. Put yourself down. These thoughts are all learnt from people in your past, the environments you were in &are in, or the way you viewed situations.
.
Here's a more supportive way to speak to yourself.
Notice if you have not been kind to yourself such as the self talk above👆
.
❤I UNDERSTAND 🤗you need to cry, this IS tough & emotions are normal, you need to allow yourself to let that out. Maybe not now but later on schedule a sad film or song to have a good😓
.
❤I must CHAMPION myself. If i don't know then I've not learnt it, I am capable of learning anything, I must look for ways to do that. 
.
❤I FEEL anxious. What is my body trying to tell me? What do I need? Water, breathe a break? Etc. I CAN stop to action what I need to feel calmer.
. 
❤I keep finding myself in the SAME situation. I am GOING TO look at my patterns or thought-feelings-behaviour to find out what I do to keep being here. Then I can change that(TRY CBT)
.
❤DISTRACT -what made me smile? what does cheer me up? Let's do that NOW.
.
#anxiety #selftalk #cbt

node.text:
You need stories of 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲, because any fear causes anxiety, & if you want to feel less anxious this is helpful👇
.
🎨@theopeninvite
✒@anxiety_wellbeing 
.
Strange huh? That fear causes anxiety & anxiety causes fear.

Well you need fear because in an emergency you don't want to be stopping to have a cup of tea. But, because anxiety causes fear you can very easily become afraid of anxiety, hence why you feel stuck. There is a way out, contact me for coaching if you would like a hand but first.
.
In my 20's I had my second panic attack, first one wasn't that bad & I coped but the second, was too much.
.
I became afraid of everything, & I mean everything, outside, people, food, breathing, my thoughts, my body, going out, going down stairs, telling anyone, of hurting myself. Etc. 
.
I felt like an animal backed up in a cage, nothing was helping😔I contemplated what I would do to get out, with zero skills & a belief that I would feel this way forever, I had a couple for thoughts of how I could get out, leave this world. Lasted about a minute but I was too afraid to do that. Good job too.
.
It was the best thought I could of had because it made me realise that telling the doctor could not be as bad as this. Even if my fears were realised & they said I would need to go to a mental hospital (not a good rep in those days) it was still better than this!
.
You know what? My fear was not true
.
It took a process of talking, honesty.
A cbt therapist 
Leaning about anxiety, the mind, the body
Practice 
Emotional, spiritual help
Pushing through fears
Etc
.
It was a process I would never change because it has given me so much insight, insight you cannot by, or study. 
.
Enough to be able to help & guide others out of any anxiety circle & feeling more confident, grown, accepted, validated & with new skills. 
.
You can get out of a circle but you have to make the moves to do it, no matter how you  feel, look for help, if you feel you can't get it, try jot to let that thought stop you. It is possible. If you find you do not click with your medical doctor, look for another. If you dont know much about what anxiety is, stay open to all info. 
.
#anxietyhelp
